tion callbacks; it does not request runtime permissions or access protected Android APIs.\",\n695:           \"`ProfileViewModel.onEvent` propagates the logout action by toggling login state and then invoking the navigation callback, so the profile screen reacts immediately to the logout event.\",\n696:           \"`ProfileViewModel.onEvent` only toggles persisted login state and invokes the logout callback; it does not request permissions or call protected APIs.\",\n697:           \"`ProfileViewModel` has no independent load/resume teardown path; its lifecycle responsibility is limited to servicing the logout event while the profile screen is active.\",\n698:           \"`ProfileEvent.kt` defines only the `PerformLogout` callback payload and does not represent permission requests, results, or protected API access.\"\n699:         ],\n700:         \"riskHints\": [\n701:           \"critical/high behavior cannot close on build pass alone\"\n702:         ],\n703:         \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n704:           \"Closed critical/high features must record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence.\",\n705:           \"Build pass alone is not per-feature verification.\",\n706:           \"Referenced target tests need to be covered by the latest accepted test gate or explicit verificationEvidence.\"\n707:         ],\n708:         \"architectureHints\": [\n709:           \"If several source files are merged, keep business behavior discoverable through precise target endpoints.\"\n710:         ],\n711:         \"testHints\": [\n712:           \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase06_profile_capabilities_verification_test.cj::profileStorePreservesStaticIdentityAndPlaceholderActions\",\n713:           \"translation-inputs/test-build-reports/phase-06-profile-capabilities-verification/test-build-report.md: PASS `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` (entry/src/test/cangjie)\",\n714:           \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase06_profile_capab